HOSTS are any device which sends or receive traffic .Ex-Computer,Servers,phones,Cloud servers
Also iot devies-tv,speakers,thermometer,lights
Anything that sends or receives traffic over the a network are called hosts.Ex-Clients and servers

**An IP Address**-Is the identity of each host.
It is of 32 bits.
Represented as 4 octets and each octet can be 0-255.
IP address are assigned by IANA .

A Network -is what transports traffic btw hosts. Without neetwok data transfer will happen in portablre media.
A subnet, or subnetwork, is a smaller, logical subdivision of a larger network.(network within a anetwork)
